 of south carolina; columbia, sc"], "date": "1921-03-24", "dates": ["1921-03-24"], "description": ["J FULLER LYON A AppracUttM by J B Traywtcb It wa in the autumn of 1869 that I spent a night in the home of J Ful ler Lyon It wai soon after hi first marriage Ilia mother had died n few year before They were living in the old home the place of hia birth April I 1842 near Asbury church in Abbeville county a community of high ideal and fine Christian homes I had met brother Lyon ft a short while before but that evening spent in that refined home with its delight ful inmates ha ever been a precious memory to me A few years after this I became the pastor of the fam ily ft was the memorable year of 1876 and he was that year elected Probate Judge of Abbevile county Since then for forty four year I have been in touch with him in church work at district and annual confer ences as coworker and confidential friend He was treasurer of our Board of Finance for nearly forty years and his going away leaves a void in my life which can only be filled in the great beyond He was by nature possessed of"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-05-12T00:30:24.684Z", "group": ["ndnp/scu", "university-of-south-carolina-columbia-sc-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87065702/1921-03-24/ed-1/?sp=7", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dragonfruit_ver01:data:sn87065702:00516991148:1921032401:0186/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=268&w=205", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dragonfruit_ver01:data:sn87065702:00516991148:1921032401:0186/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=537&w=410", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dragonfruit_ver01:data:sn87065702:00516991148:1921032401:0186/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=1074&w=820", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dragonfruit_ver01/data/sn87065702/0